    <body>
        <p>Converts the cursor to Polyline mode, which lets you create a straight or angled line with or without an arrow at the end (which you can change or remove by double-clicking the line and using the Polyline Properties dialog). After you select this button, you can click anywhere in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic,Products.MovieSync">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> to identify the starting point for the line. When you move the cursor, a straight line segment is drawn. If you click the left mouse button, it signifies the end of that line segment and the start of another line segment. When you move the cursor, another straight line segment is drawn. You can identify the end of the line by double-clicking. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic,Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../UI_Elements/Polyline_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Polyline Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
